title: A Voyage round Great Britain; with short views of Aberdeen, Balmoral, ... Fécamp, Havre and Paris
author: Hargreaves, Thomas
snippet: In the same dock we found anotherRuncorn vessel, the ' Hilda,' just arrived, though sixdays longer out than ourselves. There was in theVictoria Dock a Government vessel with some officials on board. There are three docks in Aberdeen :the Victoria, the Albert, and the Upper Docks.

title: Black's picturesque tourist of Scotland.
snippet: These splendid works, up to May 1850, have cost £600,000, and yield an annual revenue of .£25,000. The Victoria Dock, though for some years open to vessels, is not quite completed. On the south quay of Earl Grey's dock is a large crane capable of raising 30 tons.

title: Sunny memories of foreign lands.
author: Stowe, Harriet Beecher
snippet: " All modern, though," says somebody, in tones of disappointment. Now we are passing the Victoria Dock. Bang, bang, again.

title: My first visit to Europe:
author: Dickinson, Andrew
snippet: It was Jiiverpool in the distance. Before daylight I was safely moored in the Victoria Dock.
